title="Alex Nelson">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>We see from <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[0+0=0]]></fr:tex> that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(0+0)\star  x=0\star  x]]></fr:tex>. But distributivity rewrites the left-hand side as <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(0\star  x)+(0\star  x)=0\star  x]]></fr:tex>, then subtracting <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[0\star  x]]></fr:tex> from both sides gives us <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[0\star  x=0]]></fr:tex> as desired.</fr:p>
<fr:p>Similarly, from <fr:tex
